700,424,Workorder,"How can corrective work orders for Chiller 9 (CWC04009) be bundled to optimize the maintenance schedule for 2017, 2018, and 2019, with a bundle duration of two weeks and a minimum of two work orders per bundle, along with bundle details?",Decision Support,False,"There will be three bundles generated with the size of 15, 6 and 2 respectively.  Suggest bundles of corrective work orders for CWC04009 across 2017–2019, ensuring each bundle contains at least two work orders scheduled within a two-week window.",prescriptive,Chiller,Source: Maintenance operations; Non-deterministic query allowing multiple valid responses; Category: Decision Support,paraphrase,,,2025-01-19T01:12:02
701,424,Workorder,"Provide guidance on grouping corrective work orders for equipment CWC04009 (Chiller 9) across 2017-2019 into bundles that are within a two-week window and contain at least two work orders, including details of the bundles.",Decision Support,False,"There will be three bundles generated with the size of 15, 6 and 2 respectively.  Suggest bundles of corrective work orders for CWC04009 across 2017–2019, ensuring each bundle contains at least two work orders scheduled within a two-week window.",prescriptive,Chiller,Source: Maintenance operations; Non-deterministic query allowing multiple valid responses; Category: Decision Support,paraphrase,,,2025-08-01T00:03:51
702,424,Workorder,"What is the optimal way to bundle corrective work orders for Chiller 9 with ID CWC04009 for the years 2017 to 2019, such that each bundle is within a two-week period and has a minimum of two work orders, and what are the details of these bundles?",Decision Support,False,"There will be three bundles generated with the size of 15, 6 and 2 respectively.  Suggest bundles of corrective work orders for CWC04009 across 2017–2019, ensuring each bundle contains at least two work orders scheduled within a two-week window.",prescriptive,Chiller,Source: Maintenance operations; Non-deterministic query allowing multiple valid responses; Category: Decision Support,paraphrase,,,2025-04-26T09:08:21
703,507,multiagent,Predict the energy consumption of Chiller 9 for the week starting 2020-04-27 using data from MAIN site.,Knowledge Query,True,"The expected response should confirm the successful execution of all required actions, ensuring that the correct asset ('Chiller 9'), location (MAIN), and time range (week of 2020-04-27) were used for data retrieval and analysis. It should specify that the agent identified the sensor name (power input sensor) and retrieved the historical energy consumption data for Chiller 9 during the specified time period. The response must also explain that the agent attempted to analyze the data for energy consumption prediction, but was unable to do so due to insufficient data, as the power input for Chiller 9 was consistently 0.0 from 2020-04-20 to 2020-04-25, indicating that the chiller was not operating.",predictive,Chiller,Source: Multi-agent coordination requirements; Deterministic query with single correct answer; Category: Knowledge Query,paraphrase,,,2025-09-14T04:06:06
704,223,TSFM,Analyze 'Chiller 9 Condenser Water Flow' sensor data from 'data/tsfm_test_data/chiller9_tsad-small.csv' using multiple methods.,Complex Query,True,The forecasting results for 'Chiller 9 Condenser Water Flow' using data in 'data/tsfm_test_data/chiller9_annotated_small_test.csv' are available in the json file and results of anomaly detection are stored in a csv file,retrospective,Chiller,Source: Time series forecasting needs; Deterministic query with single correct answer; Category: Complex Query,paraphrase,,,2025-08-29T20:21:57
705,425,Workorder,What methods can I use to examine multiple KPI anomalies and identify the underlying cause of the problems?,Decision Support,False,"Based on the utilzied LLM, the process begins with collecting and cleaning historical KPI and maintenance data, followed by detecting anomalies across key performance indicators. These anomalies are then analyzed for correlations, leading to root cause hypotheses that are validated with logs and expert input, ultimately guiding the bundling of corrective work orders into optimized maintenance actions. Provide a method to analyze anomalies across multiple KPIs for more accurate root cause diagnosis.",prescriptive,Equipment,Source: Maintenance operations; Non-deterministic query allowing multiple valid responses; Category: Decision Support,paraphrase,,,2026-02-28T00:50:14
706,413,Workorder,"Using the predict_next_work_order_probability function, what is the likelihood of the next work order for equipment CWC04009 as of 2018-01-02?",Prediction,True,"Freon Management (code MT012) under Maintenance and Routine Checks has a probability of 0.2. The output should have the probability for primary code.  For example, the highest probability of next work order.  The expected response should be able to use historical work order data up to 2018-01-02 for CWC04009 to identify or predict the next work order probability, ensuring no cutoff of results. More specific, It should be a list of work order with the probabilities (the summation of the probabilities should be one).",predictive,Equipment,The output token size changed to 2000 to make sure there is no cut-off of the generated results.,paraphrase,,,2025-01-12T02:39:12
